  "title": "Assembly Technician",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p>• Perform magnet and Ensat assembly according to work instructions and standards</p><p>• Handle small and magnet parts carefully</p><p>• Ensure correct alignment, orientation, and placement of magnets and Ensat inserts.</p><p>• Carry out Ensat insertion accurately using the required tools and methods.</p><p>• Carry out basic visual inspection to ensure product quality and accuracy</p><p>• Follow standard operating procedures (SOP) and safety guidelines</p><p>• Maintain a clean and organized work area</p><p>• Report any defects or abnormalities promptly</p><p>• Other ad-hoc duties as assigned<br /></p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>• Meticulous, careful, and detail-oriented</p><p>• Positive attitude and willingness to learn</p><p>• Able to follow instructions accurately</p><p>• No prior experience required (training will be provided)</p><p>• Suitable for entry-level candidates</p><p>• Willing to work in Woodlands area<br /></p><p><u><strong>Benefit:</strong></u></p><p>• Annual Leave</p><p>• Medical Benefit</p><p>• Air Con Working Environment</p><p>• Work Life Balance</p><p>• Friendly Working Environment</p>",
